reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for listening only
reviews.reviewText: I have tried these on multiple phones, same result. Listener has horrible experience. The headset creates horrible static and crackling. I have tried them directly to the phone and through c type adapters. On my side as the listener, i hear nothing. But i have tested this after multiple people complained about connection. I got a new phone and tested with my previous phone. Whichever had the headset was fine and the listening experience was awful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Thought these were apple and they are not. Read carefully, they say apple but again, no! I didn't realize it until the arrived and I took them out of the package. Immediately knew they weren't apple because the logo was not on the back of the case. They sound pretty good for the length of time they last which is not very long. Very cheaply made and will not ever purchase these again. Good for kids if you don't want to spend alot if they get ruined. I've had better luck from the dollar tree. That says it all. I do not recommend if your looking for good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for. (But you deserve better, pay more for something that is better quality)
reviews.reviewText: When removed from their non-branded funky art shipping box these wired earbuds are dead ringers for Apple wired earbuds right down to the plastic film used to ‘protect’ and securely close the plastic case they come in, but that’s where any similarity ends. The materials used feel and are of significantly lesser quality; as also appears to be the product and packaging assembly.Removing the earbuds from the packaging required some effort due to not being wrapped well. One of the wires was severely and permanently crimped/bent in half. I thought the earbud would not work due to broken wiring, but surprisingly it did. The volume control and mic were nonfunctional. Their sound is mediocre and somewhat muddy. Fortunately, my use case is to listen to spoken word podcasts so they are adequate and I will use them until the die which could be a long while or very soon. When they do, I will not be buying these again.For the price I was not expecting anything resembling Apple quality or performance, but I was expecting better than what these wired earbuds delivered. I rolled the dice and paid the price. I will not be making this mistake again.
